snippet.title: PM Modi's campaign keeps NDA in race; Has tired-retired pitch hurt Nitish? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On Newshour Special Edition today, Navika Kumar discusses the numbers of exit poll results which have come to light after the final phase of Bihar Elections 2020 and also the key takeaways from the exit polls.

Times Now C-Voter Poll gives 116 seats to the NDA, 120 seats to the UPA, one goes to Chirag Paswan’s LJP and 6 seats to other parties. The Poll of Polls also suggests that the Mahagathbandhan could conquer the Bihar throne this year.

Will Modi-Nitish alliance triumph? Or will Mahagathbandhan string an upset?

While Sudhanshu Trivedi, National BJP Spokesperson & MP, BJP lauds Chief Minister Nitish Kumar’s leadership in Bihar. JDU Spokesperson Rajib Ranjan the development took place so far in Bihar under Nitish Kumar’s regime.

snippet.title: Is Donald Trump only efficient in dealing with China & Pak and not economy? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
In this episode of Newshour Debate, Madhavdas talks about another crucial election that has kickstarted today in the United States. The U.S Presidential Elections have begun today onwards and with this, the race to the White House is going to end soon. While Donald Trump chose the self-congratulatory mode to woo the voters one last time, Joe Biden got the support from Former President Barack Obama and various celebs. Who will win the elections this time? Will the U.S bring back Donald Trump or will Joe Biden take the charge? 

To discuss the first polls, Madhavdas is joined on the panel with Shalabh Kumar, Chidanand Rajghatta, and Anita Kumar. Anita says that the relationship between India & America was pretty good when Joe Biden was the Vice President. Shalabh Kumar adds to this and says when it comes to China & Pakistan, Donald Trump is better, but when it comes to the economy, Joe Biden is better.

snippet.title: Supriya Sule in a soup over poll affidavit; Did she betray trust of voters? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar exposes yet another massive political newsbreak. Discrepancies in NCP MP Supriya Sule’s affidavit have come to light. In the affidavit, shareholding details of her husband Sadanand Sule have been allegedly omitted.

Tax sleuths probing affidavit found undisclosed assets as well. The probe report will be soon sent to the Election Commission. Earlier, the similar allegations were put against Maharashtra Chief Minister Uddhav Thackeray’s son Aditya Thackeray.

Countering the allegations, Supriya Sule claims it as an inadvertent error. Did Supriya Sule betray trust if voters?

While Political Analyst Deepak Yogi says ‘This is a big expose, but at the same time I want to say that Smriti Irani has been accused of misrepresenting her educational qualifications’, lawyer Shehzad says ‘The Election Commission of India, which is a Constitutional authority, is overseeing all of this. Ergo, it is not just the CBI or the ED which is probing this’.

Watch!

snippet.title: PM Modi & Rahul Gandhi's fight for Bihar explodes; Who is leading the battle? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar talks about the political fight which heated up in Bihar after Prime Minister Narendra Modi entered the battlefield. This happened just five days before the first phase of polling in Bihar. PM Modi and Congress’ Rahul Gandhi led rallied across the State.

PM Modi addressed three rallies, whereas, Rahul Gandhi addresses only two. Their speeches were focusing on the problems faced by kisans, jawans and shramiks in the State. While Prime Minister took a dig on the Mahagathbandhan accusing the party of fraud, Rahul Gandhi countered back with exploding the migrant mess which erupted amid lockdown.

Senior Journalist Sheela shares her views over the surging political dispute in Bihar. She says ‘Fight in Bihar elections which Tejashwi Yadav is giving, is not a big surprise. Bihar is a very tough state & the present Government has been ruling the state for the past 15 years’.

Watch!

snippet.title: BJP manifesto vows free COVID vaccine, but oppositions slam opportunism? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar discusses a promise made by the ruling party only a few days ahead of the Bihar Elections. The Bhartiya Janata Party released a manifesto, in which they promised distribution of free COVID-19 vaccines in Bihar. However, the vaccine will be granted to the citizens, only if the party wins elections.

BJP’s poll promise to donate free COVID-19 vaccines has sparked a row and opposition parties have lashed out, slamming opportunism and claiming promise as a bribe. But, is BJP promising vaccine for votes as ire against Nitish Kumar stings alliance?

RJD’s Spokesperson Nawal Kishore says ‘Free vaccine is a welcome step, but it should not be made a political issue, neither should it be included as the 1st agenda in a poll manifesto’

While Political Analyst Dusyant Naagar questions ‘What is BJP doing? They'll give vaccines to people only if they get votes?’

In defence to this, BJP Spokesperson Samit Patra says ‘The scenario in Bihar will change to a large extent when PM Modi hits the ground tomorrow’

Watch!

snippet.title: Kashmiris stage Anti-Pakistan protest; Why is Gupkar Lobby silent on this? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar talks about unprecedented scenes which occurred in Srinagar on the day of Pakistan’s 1947 Kashmir invasion. Protests were staged against the Pakistan Jehad narrative. The invasion was later called as a ‘Black Day’. Kashmiris observe black day and send a message to Pakistan that Kashmiris do not approve of the proxy invasion of 1948 by Pak Army and tribal.
Srinagar Street witnessed loud pro-India chants. Along with this anti-Pakistan chants were also heard. The enchanting voice of local citizens was completely ignored by the Gupkas Lobby. Questions were raised against the Gupkar Lobby who tried to revoke Article 370.
'Is nail in coffin for Azadi narrative?'
While Senior Journalist Aarti Tikoo says ‘ In 1947, Pak Army plundered Kashmir, raped not just Kashmir Hindu/Sikh/Muslim women, but also Christian nuns. Everyone in Kashmir should be taught this history’, BJP National Spokesperson Sambit Patra claims ‘Only a few days ago, Farooq Abdullah said that Article 370 will be reinstated with the help of China’.
Journalist Majid Hyderi, on the other hand, says ‘It is hypocrisy on the part of BJP to observe this day as a Black Day & to forget the day when 20 Indian soldiers were killed by Chinese in Ladakh’. He further goes on to question that ‘Why is that day not observed as a Black Day’?

snippet.title: Bihar Poll tracker REVEALS jolting results; Who leads the popularity chart? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar demonstrates the ground-zero battle which is currently under in the State of Bihar. The upcoming elections are resulting in the eruption of massive political disputes, alliances and war for power. On one hand, we have the Modi-Nitish Jodi which will start its campaign soon and on another hand, we have the Mahagathbhandhan to compete against the ruling party.

Amid this political chaos, Times Now brings you results of C-Voter Poll, a survey to track the upcoming Bihar election. The questions asked in the survey were 'How satisfied are you with the performance of CM Nitish?' and 'How satisfied are you with the performance of PM Modi?'

According to the results, for Nitish Kumar, 27.43% were Very Satisfied, 31.54% were Somewhat Satisfied and 40.42% were Not Satisfied; Whereas for PM Modi, 47.06% were Very Satisfied, 28.45% were Somewhat Satisfied and 24.29% were Not Satisfied.

The Founder & Chief Editor C-Voter, Mr YR Deshmukh says that ‘We should wait to see the big surprise in Bihar this time’.

While the debate over C-Voter Poll Results gets heated, JD(U) leader Ajay Alok says ‘I don't think there is any kind of anti-incumbency for Nitish Kumar’ and SP Spokesperson Ghanshyam Tiwari says ‘The poll promise of 10 lakh jobs is creating momentum in favour of Tejashwi Yadav & catching NDA by surprise’.

According to the results, for Nitish Kumar, 27.43% were Very Satisfied, 31.54% were Somewhat Satisfied and 40.42% were Not Satisfied; Whereas for PM Modi, 47.06% were Very Satisfied, 28.45% were Somewhat Satisfied and 24.29% were Not Satisfied.

The Founder & Chief Editor C-Voter, Mr YR Deshmukh says that ‘We should wait to see the big surprise in Bihar this time’.

While the debate over C-Voter Poll Results gets heated, JD(U) leader Ajay Alok says ‘I don't think there is any kind of anti-incumbency for Nitish Kumar’ and SP Spokesperson Ghanshyam Tiwari says ‘The poll promise of 10 lakh jobs is creating momentum in favour of Tejashwi Yadav & catching NDA by surprise’.

snippet.title: PM Modi's Aatmanirbharta move pays off, but Opposition still doubts? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar discusses how India is slowing turning adverse to the Aatmanirbharta Movement led by Prime Minister Narendra Modi. The movement was launched amid two major circumstances, first the standoff dispute with China and second the outbreak of Coronavirus.

Government report suggests that after Prime Minister Narendra Modi’s ‘Go-Local’ Policy boosted, India witnessed a rise of 26% in exports and a fall of 24% in Imports. As the Atmanirbharta push paying off, is India on target to challenge China?’

While SP Spokesperson Ghanshyam Tiwari says ‘BJP has been a 'companion' of China throughout this 7 years of NDA Government’, BJP Spokesperson Nupur Sharma counters the statement saying ‘India is 22.28% higher than Bangladesh in terms of PPP per capita GDP’.

CPI (M) Leader Dr Fuad Halim, on the other hand, questions ‘Who has seen a single paise of the Rs 20 lakh crore package that was announced by PM Modi?’

snippet.title: India leads quad from the front, China isolated in its own backyard? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar talks about a diplomatic and strategic coup, led by Prime Minister Narendra Modi, which gives a mega signal to expansionist China for the first time in thirteen years. Australia has finally agreed to sail together with India US and Japan.
After thirteen years, Australia will join the upcoming Malabar exercise which effectively means that all the four-member countries of the 'Quad' or Quadrilateral coalition will be participating in the mega drill. 
Unprecedented alliance rattles Beijing. Has ‘China isolated in its own backyard?’ 
While Retired Defence Expert Ashok Mehta says ‘This can never be a military alliance unless India is prepared to forfeit its strategic autonomy, and Former Chief of Army Ved Malik says ‘ Australia joining the Malabar exercise is a major step because there was a time when they didn’t have any agreement with India on security issues’, Former Foreign Secretary, on the other hand, says ‘Japan’s inclusion in the exercise was much more important than Australia’s inclusion politically, geopolitically’.

snippet.title: Opposition slams PM Modi's warning; BJP: What's wrong in putting lives first? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar demonstrates how the opposition parties of India lashed out at Prime Minister Narendra Modi after he delivered his address to the nation on COVID-19 outbreak. BJP countered this with a direct question asking ‘What wrong with putting lives first?’

PM addressed the nation today, for the seventh time this year, on various concerns revolving around the pandemic. This included India’s fight for the vaccine, economic revival, the celebration of festivals amid Coronavirus scare, lockdown crisis and much more.

Why did the Opposition hit out at PM Modi over his address to the nation?

While Author Anand Ranganathan says ‘It was important for the PM to come out & tell India to be careful and take all health precautions. And even more important for him to say as he did that lockdown is over’, SP Spokesperson Ghanshyam Tiwari sarcastically says ‘I must congratulate BJP that today’s message of PM doesn’t shock the country’.

The debate also takes a turn as new discussions emerge. On one hand, Padma Bhushan & Chairman of Fortis Escorts Heart Institute Dr Ashok Seth says ‘When we talk about this peak gradually coming down & flattening, it’s only related to the precautions that have been taken until now’, CPI (M) Senior Leader Suneet Chopra questions ‘What has the PM done about food, unemployment?’.

snippet.title: Bengaluru Riots: Is Congress which escaped in 1984, finally exposed in 2020? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar lays out proofs which will certainly jolt the Indian National Congress. 69 days after the terrible Bengaluru Riots, proofs of Congress’ involvement in the violence have come to light. Ahead of this surprising exposure, BJP has hit out at Congress.

Times Now has accessed exclusive digital evidence which includes call data records of Congress workers. The cell phone data pins down Congress plotter. Earlier Riots’ prime victim, Congress’ MLA Akhand Srinivas Murthy has claimed that the riots were instigated by some of his party leader for revenge purpose and now the claim is proved.

Why is Congress trying to hide its involvement in the Bengaluru Riots?

BJP MP & National Spokesperson, Sudhandu Trivedi says ‘Congress should officially take a stand. Either they stand by Akhanda Srinivas Murthy or by Sampath Raj’ and Lawyer Shehzad claims ‘Har dangai ke saath, Congress ka haath’.

Whereas Islamic Scholar Atiq Ur Rehman says, ‘I do not believe in Bengaluru Police’.

snippet.title: Gandhis marched to Hathras for Dalit, but silent over Dalit dishonor in Dabra? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar discusses a jolting remark made by Former Madhya Pradesh Chief Minister Kamal Nath. Congress’ Kamal Nath allegedly referred a Dalit BJP Cabinet Leader Imarti Devi to an ‘item’.

After former MP CM Kamal Nath’s ‘item’ comment, Imarti Devi, who has been an Indian National Congress’ soldier for 23 years before joining the BJP, has questioned ‘will Sonia Gandhi allow this?’. She also stated ‘Kamal Nath should resign from the party and I will make him apologise’.

BJP has lashed out at the Congress Party for their hypocrisy. By comparing this incident to the Hathras incident, where Gandhis had marched to a meet a Dalit rape victim, the BJP has questioned the authenticity of the Dalit leader’s insult. They even asked Sonia Gandhi to take cognizance of this matter.

‘Gandhis marched to Hathras for Dalit lives, but silent over Dalit dishonour in Dabra?’

While Political Analyst Tehseen Poonawalla speaks about the derogatory language used by BJP leaders, BJP MP & National Spokesperson Sudhanshu Trivedi says ‘If a word is spoken, it is not just a word but also the tone & tenor, reference & context’.

Political Analyst Deepak Yogi, on the other hand, stated ‘Kamal Nath has not named anyone. Imarti Devi is playing ‘victim card’. Both men & women have an equal place in society’.

WATCH!

snippet.title: Congress allots ticket to Maskoor Usmani; Why is party backing 'Tukde Backer'? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
In The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar illustrates news which has come in as a huge embarrassment for the Indian National Congress. Just twelve days ahead of Bihar Elections Congress decided to allot election ticket to Maskoor Ahmad Usmani.

snippet.title: Court directs Sanjay Bhandari's extradition; Robert Vadra to face ED heat too? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar talks about the trouble that is mounting for the Gandhi Damaad Robert Vadra. The Delhi High Court has directed the Enforcement Directorates expedite the extradition of Vadra’s close aide Sanjay Bhandari, who is an arms dealer, in a money laundering case.

This development completely demolishes the defence set for Robert Vadra. Vadra’s name cropped up in the case after his emails with Sanjay Bhandari’s close aide from April 2010 came to light. The mails were about a London property. Hence, Vadra is now under the ED scanner, a chargesheet has also been filed.

Sharing his views on ED’s chargesheet against Sanjay Bhandari, Lawyer Shehzad says, ‘Today we are getting to know that Sanjay Bhandari was nothing but a front for the 1st family of corruption. Bhandari got all his deals done during UPA Government’.

While Political Analyst Tehseen Poonawalla says, ‘Whenever PM Modi is in trouble, Robert Vadra is one of his ace cards, Political Analyst Political Analyst, on the other hand, says ‘BJP has not done anything against Robert Vadra since 2014’.

snippet.title: Congress OPPOSES Kumbh Mela; Is party provoking minorities? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar presents a political dispute which has sparked massive controversy throughout the country. After Assam Chief Minister Sarbananda Sonowal announced the shutdown of Madrassas in the state, Indian National Congress’s leader came up with another buzzing statement.
Congress’ Udit Raj posted a tweet, where he opposed the celebration and the funding provided by Uttar Pradesh Government for Kumbh Mela. In counter to this, BJP has lashed out at the opposition saying ‘This statement is an insult of faith and festivals. 
Udit Raj was the same person who had made inappropriate comments on the Karauli Priest’s murder case by comparing it to Hathras Gang-Rape Case. Puja, pujari, now pilgrimage, is the opposition trying to provoke religious sentiments of Hindus?
While SP Spokesperson Ghanshyam Tiwari says, ‘Udit Raj has spent more time in BJP than Congress’, Political Analyst Dr Abbas says, ‘Congress has a ‘disease’ that it wants to see Hindu-Muslim together’, BJP’s Sambit Patra claims that Udit Raj is one of the future presidents of Indian National Congress.

snippet.title: Assam makes historic secular step, but Opposition slams the reform; Why? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar talks about a controversial decision taken by Assam Chief Minister to promote secularism. CM Sarbananda Sonowal ordered shut down of Madrassas in the State. However, while BJP lauded the end of appeasement, the opposition Party slammed the secular reform.
As our guest today we have Assam Education Minister Himanta Biswa who explains the new secular reform led by the State Government. He says, ‘Government of Assam is spending over ₹ 200 Crores on state-run Madrassas which are in turn teaching the Quran. There is demand from many other communities to run similar schools. Gita is a book which reflects India’s culture and ethos, It cannot be compared to running Madrassas’. 
BJP IT Cell Head Amit Malviya says, ‘There is no overlapping of state and religion in India. Assam has been ruled by the Congress for a large part of the last 7 decades. Funding Madrassas was a minority appeasing tactic’ 
Whereas Islamic Scholar Ilyas Sharafuddin says, ‘I have been in favour of modernisation in Madrassas for last 20 years. Both Congress and BJP have not paid attention to Madrassas’.
Political Analyst Tehseen Poonawalla says, ‘Rajendra Prasad, India’s first President studied in a Madrassa. It is not compulsory for those who are not Muslims to study the Quran. This debate is being created in 2020 only as a distraction’.
WATCH!

snippet.title: Leftists' Pakistan Dalal link crops up; Is lobby’s fight for right sponsored? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar demonstrates a sensational disclosure made by the National Investigation Agency which linked BHIMA-Koregaon accused Gautam Navlakha to the Pakistan ISI. NIA claims that Gautam backed separatists and Kashmir ‘Azadi’, a fight for rights of Urban Naxals.

Times Now accesses the chargesheet which cites a US Court order that states, Gautam Navlakha was introduced to an ISI General by a man called Gulam Fai. Fai has been now convicted in the US Court. Now, leftists links have emerged in the alleged terrorism. Is lobby’s fight for right sponsored?

While BJP IT Cell Head Amit Malviya says, ‘Navlakha has been on record on several occasions encouraging Naxals. This man has done everything that is not in the interest of the country including supporting Kashmir referendum’

Political Analyst Tehseen Poonawalla says, ‘If this is the basis of conviction, then by the same logic Ajit Doval was dropping terrorists off to Pakistan. Does the NIA have the evidence to link Navlakha to the case except for a letter about which they haven't been able to convince the court for the last two years?’.

snippet.title: Fake TRP scam exposed; How will the government deal with the viewership mess? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate, we talk to the Union Information and Broadcasting Minister Prakash Javadekar about the recent Fake-TRP scam. 
Prakash Javadekar clarified that BARC is managed by broadcasters directly, it is their creation and if there is a problem in the system, they should rectify it. He further stated that Media should not be TRP driven in the first place. 

The Broadcasting Minister also declared that he has read the complaint letter which is in Marathi, and the complaint only specifies one name, even when several other names have been accused. 

He further goes on to say that the system needs to change but it is not the government’s domain. Only if the broadcasters ask us to intervene can we do something, the government should not be accused of limiting press freedom, he added. He also declared that there has to be a code of conduct for all media just like there is in politics.

snippet.title: Republic TV linked to TV ratings fixing; Collaborators arrested & confess | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate with Navika Kumar, Republic TV is among the top three channels that are being investigated for the fake Television Ratings Point scandal. The unprecedented rigging in the TRP scandal has been a massive debate that has occurred for the first time in the news television industry. 

Mumbai Police Commissioner Param Bir Singh announced in a press conference briefing that the heads of the network will be summoned soon. As per the statements by the Mumbai Police, the channel scammed the Television Ratings Point and tried to boost the viewership. 

The channel paid extra money to boost the Television Ratings Point, even people who do not understand English were asked to switch on the television for viewership. The Mumbai Police Commissioner Param Bir Singh stated an unparalleled, unrivaled, and dramatic development in the history of the television news industry.

Republic TV has now threatened to sue the Mumbai Police Commissioner for defamation and the channel has denied all the charges levelled against them. The channel issued a statement and specifically mentioned that they will file a counter case against the Mumbai Police Commissioner Param Bir Singh.

Mumbai police have disclosed the cash that was given by the Republic TV for ratings and it has gone on record. Republic TV did fix the viewership. Collaborators have now confessed and Republic TV editors have been summoned.

Police probe has sped up the TRP scam, Mumbai police will serve summons to Republic TV bosses tomorrow. BARC has submitted TRP data sought by cops. Times Now has accessed the statement of alleged 'rigged' TV owner. Nikunj Garg, Senior Editor-Internal Security explains that in this case, Mumbai police are alleging huge criminality. Aditya Raj Kaul, an independent journalist tells Navika Kumar that earlier it used to be said that 'content is the king, and now it is said that distribution is the king'.

snippet.title: Rahul Gandhi takes a dig at PM Modi; Govt counters with ‘Fact checks’ | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On the Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar discusses Congress leader Rahul Gandhi, who seems to be on an overdrive to corner the BJP government over the farm legislation. Rahul Gandhi has been protesting since the last few days, perched on the top of a tractor, fighting for the cause of farmers. Rahul Gandhi however, was seen seated on a sofa seat as claimed by the BJP on the tractor, during one of these protests. An image was made viral by the BJP in which Rahul Gandhi can be seen seated on a sofa seat, which several of BJP ministers tweeted. Rahul Gandhi took a jibe at the Prime Minister when one of the NDA ministers questioned him about the tractor image. Rahul Gandhi questioned why nothing was said when two special aircraft were delivered for the Prime Minister. 

Rahul Gandhi’s reference to the aeroplanes is in regard to the Air India One, which has been procured for the VVIPs. To discuss the same, Navika Kumar is joined by Shehzad Poonawalla, Sanjay Jha, Abbas Hafeez, Gaurav Bhatia. 

Shehzad Poonawalla states that Rahul Gandhi is always confused about the facts, whether it’s Rafale plane or this plane. Gaurav Bhatia adds to this and states that a person who has been doing his picnics on INS Viraat definitely doesn’t have the right to raise these questions. Sanjay Jha, the former Congress member, refutes these arguments and states that if Rahul Gandhi decides to get into a tractor and really make that a symbolic manifestation of farmer protest being backed by the Congress party, it should be considered good in a democracy.

snippet.title: Hathras gangrape case: Did the system conspire to cover-up & sabotage justice? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate, the gut-wrenching incident in Hathras cannot be put into words, the trauma felt by the family cannot be undone. Uttar Pradesh's government and police have not only been exposed by the horrific Hathras case but the state has also questioned how the safe are women in India today?

Hathras horror is yet another example of internalised misogyny and how women still have to create a safe space for themselves out in the open. It is important for women to be heard in political arenas. The forced cremation is yet another angle that has been a massive debate over how negligent the administration was. The family was not allowed to bid a final goodbye to their daughter.

Times Now brings to you different shreds of evidence that prove that Hathras' victim's father did not light up the pyre. The police conducted the last rites and the family was neither involved nor was consented to.

The visuals explain that the Hathras victim's cremation was done by a cop and can be seen asking if anyone wants to place firewood on the pyre. The victim's family has said that they were roughed up by the Uttar Pradesh police. Their sheer negligence and irresponsible behavior have been one of the most contested debates.

The mother of the victim from Hathras tells Navika Kumar that she did not get to see her daughter who fought a long battle. The mother then explains how brutal and irresponsible the cremation was. She says the policeman poured petrol on her dead body. She then adds that the family wanted to light her pyre.

snippet.title: Deepika named in drug chats; Why aren't B-Town celebs demanding a cleanup? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar talks about the Bollywood Industry and why a certain section of B-Town is absolutely jittery. Popular filmstar Deepika Padukone has been allegedly named in the drug nexus exposed in the Sushant Singh Rajput death case by Narcotics Control Bureau. Along with her, other A-listers like, Shraddha Kapoor, Sara Ali Khan, Madhu Mantena and more have been linked to the B-Town cartel.

The sources reveal that Shraddha Kapoor and Sara Ali khan will also be summoned tomorrow. Rakul Preet Singh, however, will be interrogated later. Sources also say that Deepika Padukone is in touch with her legal team in Delhi. The actor is allegedly staying at a resort in Goa.
Times Now makes an attempt to contact and trace Deepika Padukone to enquire about her so-called ‘maal’ chats, however, she leaves the questions unanswered. Viewers also call in from different parts of the country to share their views on Deepika’s Maal Chats.
Will the Bollywood lobby defend her?

While, Actor & Former Bigg Boss Contestant, Arshi Khan asks, ‘Why are we only targeting Deepika Padukone? What about Kangana Ranaut who had confessed about drug consumption? Actor Mukesh Khanna questions, ‘Can anyone from the industry give it in written that drugs are not there in Bollywood?’ and Actor Samir Soni says, ‘I will be a big liar if I say that at least 50-60% of Bollywood has not tried or consumed drugs’.

snippet.title: NCB glares on Karan Johar's Party; Was Mumbai Police trying to armor B-Town? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar discusses an alleged drug party video of Karan Johar that had gone viral in 2019. This video is recorded by Karan Johar himself and consists of eight Bollywood stars. SAD’s Majinder Sirsa had filed a complaint to the Mumbai Police against the supposed drug video, however, the police took no action and wilfully ignored the complaint.

Sirsa on Times Now has revealed the ignorance of Mumbai Police and 48 hours after this revelation, the Narcotics Control Bureau is going to probe the video. Sources say NCB will send the video to the Forensic Department to investigate its authenticity. The eight A-listers including Deepika Padukone, Varun Dhawan, Vicky Kaushal and more are under NCB scanner.

Was Mumbai Police trying to shield the Bollywood drug mafias?

SAD Leader Manjinder Sirsa says, ‘This video was supposed to be investigated at the 1st place in August 2019 but Mumbai Police chose not to investigate this’.

Whereas Activist Rahul Easwar says, ‘Everyone agrees that every Punjabi is not a drug addict. In the same way, everyone in Bollywood is not a drug addict’.

Meanwhile, Amidst Opposition & ‘friendly’ fire, PM slams ‘fakery’ to mislead farmers.

snippet.title: Congress sullies PM Modi's birthday; Is this a sign of social harmony? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar exposes hypocrisy of the opposition party. Today, Prime Minister Narendra Modi turns 70, BJP in order to honour the PM decided to celebrate this week as ‘Seva Saptah’. In the Sewa Saptah, there will a presentation of spectacles to the poor and needy, fruits will be distributed to patients in seventy hospitals, a donation of plasma will be held for seventy COVID-19 patients, seventy plants will be implanted in every booth, and a lot more.

However, keeping the political rivalry up, the Congress Party decided to make a personal attack dubbing PM Modi’s birthday as National ‘Unemployment Day’. The Congress, in history, has marked Former PM Jawaharlal Nehru’s birthday as ‘Bal Diwas,’ Indira Gandhi’s birthday as ‘Ekta Diwas,’ Rajiv Gandhi’s birthday as ‘Sadbhawna Diwas’ but sullied PM Modi’s birthday, WHY?

While Author Anand Ranganathan says, ‘Unemployment is a serious concern but it’s not going to be solved by Rahul Gandhi behaving like a petulant child who gatecrashed a birthday party demanding a return gift’, BJP Spokesperson says, ‘Double standards’ & ‘hypocrisy’ are the other names of the party.

snippet.title: Sushant's WhatApp chats reveal stunning disclosures; Was he silenced on June 13? | The Newshour
snippet.description:
On The Newshour today, Navika Kumar discloses a sensational scoop which will change the narrative on the Sushant Singh Rajput Death mystery. Top CBI sources have revealed how Sushant had literally dropped off the grid from 2:30 pm on the 13th of June, which is exactly 22 hours before Sushant’s body was found.

snippet.title: Rattled B-Town slanders drug probe; Who is covering-up to save the cartel? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar discusses a story which was exposed on Times Now in August but has exploded now. The Narcotics Control Bureau is closing in on the nexus between the film industry and the drug mafias.

However, some people are still moving against the probe. Actor and RS MP Jaya Bachchan made slandering comments on the investigation saying that there is ‘attempt made to malign Bollywood’. Actor turned Politician Ravi Kishan also shares his views on Jaya Bachchan’s jolting remarks, says, ‘She’s my senior and shouldn’t have said that. I am extremely hurt’.

Why and who is covering-up to save B-Town cartel?

While Actor Dilip Tahil says, ‘It’s disgrace … where’s the evidence?’, Singer & Union Minister, Supriyo babul says, ‘There cannot be smoke without fire. Rotten oranges should be punished. It’s unfortunate that SSR had to pay with his life’.

snippet.title: Attempt made to muzzle SSR's death probe; Why are agents clogging justice? | The Newshour
snippet.description:
On Newshour today, Navika Kumar talks about a desperate move made only to gag the truth unveiled by Times Now as far as Sushant Singh Rajput’s death case is concerned. In the latest move, some lawyers and ex-cops united together to file a petition in the Bombay High Court claiming “vilification of police”.
If the media hadn’t step in the case, drug angle would have still been buried, Mumbai Polices’ February inaction would’ve gone unnoticed, India wouldn’t have known about SSR’s diary, Sushant’s financial transactional would still remain suppressed, Rhea Chakraborty’s breakup chats with Mahesh Bhatt wouldn’t come to light and most importantly India wouldn’t have known the truth. 
Why are proxies blocking justice for Sushant Singh Rajput?
While, Digital Journalist, Priyanka Deo says, ‘This shows that the investigation by Mumbai Police has loopholes’. Lawyer, Vikas Gupta states, ‘You cannot bash Rhea Chakraborty’ and Political Analyst Tehseen Poonawalla says, ‘I stand by Mumbai Police, they shouldn't be targeted’.

snippet.title: SC advocate Harish Salve tears into 'Rhea Lobby' | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate with Navika Kumar, Investigators have been telling that we have not seen anything yet in the Sushant Singh Rajput's death case. snippet.title: Was Sena Sarkar behind Sushant Singh Rajput postmortem report botch-up? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate with Navika Kumar, There has been a foul play in Sushant Singh Rajput's post mortem report. There is a botch-up by the Mumbai Police. Whether inadvertently or deliberately that is something the CBI has to come over a conclusion. 

Lawyer of SSR Family Vikas Singh says, After death, everything becomes standstill. The body doesn’t digest anything thereafter. If Sushant had juice, that juice would still remain in the stomach even if there is a delay in the autopsy. Of all the important districts of Maharashtra, Copper Hospital is the nominated hospital for autopsy. 

Political Analyst Sundar Balakrishnan says, In the case of hanging if it is done in the midnight or before midnight then the delay will be already there (6-12 hrs) to conduct the post mortem.  

#SSRDeathDisclosure

snippet.title: CBI to probe SSR death case, Chetan Bhagat tells the untold story of Sushant | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate, Navika Kumar briefs the latest inputs about the CBI probe in Sushant Singh Rajput’s death case and also speaks exclusively to the celebrated Author Chetan Bhagat.
For the first time ever, Chetan Bhagat breaks silence on Sushant Singh Rajput’s tragic and mysterious demise, revealing some stunning and harsh truth of B-Town bullies.
Chetan says, ‘Sushant was funny, cute & adorable gullibility. I could never imagine he would commit suicide. Sushant Singh’s case brought back many memories. It mattered to Sushant Singh that he was a TV actor. He was devastated to see ‘blind items’ and was disturbed about molestation rumours. If you ask me, I would say that this case will go beyond the court
Bhagat even lauded the media trial of Sushant Singh Rajput’s death case saying ‘justice gets improved in any case’, but will he ‘name & shame’ bullies in Bollywood?
Watch to know!

snippet.title: Is Maharashtra Government 'buffling' Sushant Singh Rajput's Death Case? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On the Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar talks about a campaign initiated led by Times Now and its impact on the entire nation. ‘Times Now for CBI for SSR’ campaign was started only for one motive, which is, Justice for Sushant.

After 66 days of investigation and by exposing more than 100 revelations, this global movement finally resonates with the apex court. The Supreme Court pronounced its judgement on the Sushant Singh Rajput Death Case, ordering a CBI probe and giving hopes to millions on people.

But, The Maharashtra Government seems to not be in favour of the Apex. Is a parallel probe being ordered to subvert CBI? Is Uddhav Government backing Mumbai Polices’ blunder?

Rajya Sabha MP, Subramanian Swamy says, ‘The Maharashtra Government is ‘bluffing’ in Sushant Sing case. They don’t know the difference between an inquiry and an investigation. Obviously, Maharashtra Govt has something to hide, somebody has to be ‘protected’. It cannot be a suicide at all’.

Whereas, SSR Family Lawyer Advocate Vikas Singh stated, ‘There is no scope left with the Maharashtra Government to do anything ‘funny’ now. Very soon we will get justice and very soon the culprits will be brought to books’.

#TimesNowForCBIForSSR #SCBacksCBIForSSR

snippet.title: Supreme Court to deliver verdict on Sushant's case, Will CBI investigate case? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
Release Date: 19 August 2020

On the Newshour Debate today, Navika Kumar discusses the latest developments in Sushant Singh Rajput’s death case and investigation. The Supreme Court will soon pronounce its verdict in the plea filed by Rhea Chakraborty demanding transfer of Sushant Singh death probe to Mumbai.
The entire nation is pleading a CBI probe. Global prayers and mass movements are taking place across the world. Will the Apex Court give justice to Sushant Singh Rajput?
‘Everyone wants a transparent probe in this case. I've been receiving pictures of billboards put up in countries like Bangladesh, U.S, Australia, etc. demanding justice for Sushant Singh’ says Advocate Ishkaran Bhandari. While BLP National Spokesperson, Sambit Patra says, ‘‘When we see too much of callousness, it is not coincidental, but natural that the fingers point towards a conspiracy. We want the conspiracy to be unearthed’.
Whereas, Political Analyst, Tehseen Soonawalla says, ‘When a Zero FIR was filed in Bihar, they ought to have transferred it to Mumbai. Now, either Maharashtra Government should recommend a CBI probe or the court should decide. Bihar Government can't decide’.

#TimesNowForCBIForSSR

snippet.title: Powerful Mafia behind Sushant Singh Rajput probe 'Cover-up'? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate with Navika Kumar, 60 days after Sushant Singh Rajput's death, suicide 'theory' totally nailed as all leads allegedly point to a 'murder'. Here are the four unseen new videos that nail 'lies'. 

A Ranganathan, Author says that if the investigation was proceeding as it should, why did Rhea Chakraborty ask for a transfer of the case to CBI. 

Nishant Verma, a Political Analyst, says that everyone is trying to jump to a conclusion, in this case, I understand that the truth should be brought forth.

A Ranganathan then explains how there are stunning parallels between Sushant Singh Rajput and Jessica Lal's murder case. Many debates have now come up over the course of his death investigation and it has not only sparked tension in Bollywood but also within states and governments. The political tension of the case has increased nationwide doubt over what to believe in and will justice ever be provided to the late actor?

snippet.title: Why is Shiv Sena desperate to cover-up Sushant Singh Rajput's truth? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate with Madhavdas G, we discuss the most detailed and relentless investigation in Sushant Singh Rajput probe. Is an attempt being made by the Maharashtra Government to silent the family of late Sushant Singh Rajput's family? How an attempt has been made by the ShivSena government towards the family of the late actor Sushant Singh Rajput. 

Shocking new twist emerges in Sushant Singh death probe. Sushant’s family threatened. 

Sushant’s father has the right to file an FIR in Bihar and nobody denies that. Mumbai Police is the best Police Force in this country and has a higher conviction rate than CBI. says, Political Analyst Tehseen Poonawalla.

Let us talk about what a common man of this country would feel if he sees a powerful politician telling him in a case where he is a victim to ‘keep quiet.’ Mumbai Police hasn’t even started the investigation in Sushant case yet. says, Advocate Ishkaran Singh Bhandari.

#SenaTargetsSSRFamily

snippet.title: Sushant Singh Rajput Probe: Insulting legacy & ignoring proof to deny justice? | The Newshour Debate
snippet.description:
On The Newshour Debate with Navika Kumar, If you haven't read the words of Sushant Singh Rajput, 'Gulshan' for his family. you haven't read anything. the soul of this young man, who seems to have cut-off from his own life suddenly was expressed in his diary. snippet.title: Gandhi trust- Zakir files EXPOSED; Why was Naik's donation hidden? | The Newshour Debate (23 July)
snippet.description:
Original Release Date: 24 July 2020

On the Newshour Debate with Navika Kumar-

We discuss this sensational expose on the Rajiv Gandhi Charitable trust. Thie Gandhi family charitable trust has received ₹50 lakh from Zakir Naik's IRF (Islamic Research Foundation.) 
Times Now has all the documents, bank transactional entries of this money that was transferred to the Rajiv Gandhi Charitable trust.

After the NIA registered a case against Zakir Naik, this money was returned. On the fraud of parliament, I&B Minister Manish Tewari, in 2012 came out and said that Zakir Naik's Peace TV was among many other illegal foreign channels whose content was not conducive to India security environment. 

This declaration was made during the UPA era under the Cabinet of Prime Minister Manmohan Singh and was also very close to the Gandhi Family. Even after that, the Gandhi family didn't return the money back in 2012. The money was returned in 2016 when he had already fled the country and the NIA registered the case.

Law Minister Ravi Shankar Prasad in 2016 had questioned the Congress party about these funds but they didn't return it then. They waited till the NIA registered a case against him.

Why was the donation kept hidden for 5 years? 

#GandhiZakirFile

snippet.title: Sonia Gandhi & Shiv Sena giving 'Islamists' a pedestal? | The Newshour debate
snippet.description:
On Newshour Debate with Navika Kumar, PM Narendra Modi had a telephonic conversation with US President Donald Trump. Trump extended an invitation to PM Modi to attend the next G-7 Summit to be held in the USA.

‘Having opted to work with the PFI, over and above all other, more credible Muslim organizations, hasn't the Sonia Gandhi- Shiv Sena's appeasement politics taken an extreme turn?’

‘Should one be surprised about the Sonia Gandhi- Shiv Sena's reliance on the PFI, given how its student wing SDPI & Indian National Congress allegedly had an allegedly tacit electoral understanding ahead of the Karnataka polls in 2018?’
The PFI which has got orders to facilitate the burial of deceased Muslims in Mumbai is an NGO. It’s Popular Front India & not Popular Front of India: Sanjay Gupta, Political Analyst. 

The cyclone Nisarga has hit the Mumbai coasts and the evacuation process is undergoing at the moment.
